The darkness was now so deep that Cody was forced to take his hand out of his bag and trail it lightly along the wall
beside him. He felt certain he had missed no side passages. "Anyone that lives here must be able to see in the dark,"
he said to himself. "That gives them an advantage over me." He considered this for a moment. "But they'll be counting
on that advantage," he reasoned, "so that gives me an advantage!" He was pretty sure there was a flaw somewhere in that
argument, but felt no desire to search for it.
